##What is Inheritance
Inheritance allows one class to acquire properties and methods of another class.

It helps in code reuse.

Java uses the keyword extends.

Package Structure (Eclipse)
package inheritance;

Files: Animal.java Dog.java Main.java

Animal.java
package inheritance;

public class Animal {

    public void sound(){
        System.out.println("Animal makes sound");
    }

}
package inheritance;

public class Dog extends Animal {

    public void bark(){
        System.out.println("Dog barks");
    }

}
package inheritance;

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Dog d = new Dog();

        d.sound();
        d.bark();

    }

Output

Animal makes sound
Dog barks
}
